-- Wal-Mart says CEO of global procurement resigns
-- 
-- Mon Jan 8, 2007 2:17pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/08/businesspro-walmart-jackson-dc-idUSWEN192820070108

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Wal-Mart Stores Inc. ( WMT.N ) said on 
Monday that Lawrence Jackson, its president and chief executive 
officer of global procurement, has resigned. 

  The world's largest retailer said Jeff Macho was promoted 
to senior vice president of global procurement, effective 
immediately. Macho, who is based in Shenzhen, China, will 
report to Wal-Mart Vice Chairman John Menzer.  The retailer said Jackson, whose resignation is effective 
February 9, will stay with the company until then to help with 
the transition.